<div id="c20">
<p>I have an even more efficient way to deal with email that I discovered in, admittedly, a moment of severe frustration; just delete them all.  If ever a pile gets so long that I can&#8217;t even remember when I stopped completing items, I&#8217;ll delete them all.</p>

<p>If the information is truly that important, then either it&#8217;ll be resent in one form or another back to you, or you&#8217;ll eventually be prompted to go out and search for it out of necessity.</p>

